+Build these functions:
+
+1. overlapping_window(m1, m2)
+Return overlap start/end times or None.
+
+2. severity_from_distance(distance, safety_distance)
+distance <= 40% threshold = high
+distance <= 70% threshold = medium
+else low
+
+3. predict_conflict(m1, m2, safety_distance=5.0, time_step=0.5)
+
+Logic:
+- Check overlapping mission times
+- If no overlap return {"status":"clear"}
+- Sweep time from overlap start to end
+- Get both drone positions
+- Measure distance
+- If within threshold return:
+
+{
+ "status":"conflict",
+ "conflict_time": round(time,2),
+ "distance": round(distance,2),
+ "position_a": position tuple,
+ "position_b": position tuple,
+ "severity": level
+}
+
+- Else return {"status":"clear"}
+
+4. batch_check(primary_mission, other_missions, safety_distance=5.0)
+
+Return list of all conflicts.
+
+Keep code clean, typed, readable, no classes.

